          "reviewBody": "As a parent, I am sharing my personal experience and concerns regarding Jiva Public School Sector 21 Faridabad Haryana.\n \nFast & Overloaded Syllabus\nIn my experience, the syllabus is covered at a very fast pace. Children are often rushed through topics without adequate explanation or reinforcement, which puts unnecessary academic pressure on students.\n\n\nMismanagement & Lack of Coordination\nThere appears to be a lack of proper management and coordination between teachers and administration. Communication regarding academics, events, and student issues is often unclear or delayed.\n\n\nUnprofessional Communication\nWhen I approachd the school with genuine complaints or concerns, the way communication is handled is, at times, discouraging and unempathetic. Parents expect respectful dialogue, which unfortunately is not always felt while communicating with School.\n\nBias Between Students\nFrom what I have observed, there seems to be unequal treatment between certain students. Some children receive more attention (specially those are the kids of school staff) and support than others, which affects morale and confidence of general students.\n\n\nMismatch Between Promises & Reality\nAt the time of admission, several commitments were made regarding teaching standards, student care, and overall development. However, in practice, many of those expectations have not been fulfilled as anticipated.\n\n\nI have withdrawn the admission of my child from LKG this year, and within a single academic year, the school has changed around five teachers for the same class. Such frequent teacher turnover at the foundational level creates instability and affects young children emotionally and academically. \nFurther, as a parent, I am deeply concerned about certain disciplinary methods observed or reported by children. Some instances appeared to involve inappropriate physical handling, which is distressing being parent of 4-5 years old child . Primary students, especially at the LKG level, require patience, care, and positive reinforcement rather than strict or fear-based approaches. In view of the above experiences, I have personally decided to withdraw my child’s education at Jiva Public School in 2026 therefore got my child admission cancelled from JIva Public School. This is a decision taken purely in my child’s best interest. \nI would strongly advise other to think carefully, and evaluate all aspects thoroughly before taking an admission decision for their child.",
